              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "1USABNW"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " a 3.0 MV electrostatic tandem",
                "accelerator located within the Environmental",
                "Molecular Sciences Laboratory at Pacific Northwest",
                "National Laboratory."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The incident beam conditioner was a Goebel mirror",
                "with a 1/32 degree divergence slit. The beam height",
                "using this combination was about 0.08 mm and",
                "equatorial divergence was about 0.01 degree."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The sample used in this study was a thin amorphous",
                "carbon film (5.8 microg/cm2) on a silicate glass",
                "substrate. The  sample was examined by X-ray",
                "reflectivity (XRR) using a Philips XPert MPD system",
                " (PW3040/00 type) equipped with a Cu X-ray source",
                "operated at 1.8 kW."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Both fixed and movable surface-barrier",
                "detectors in the chamber with an energy resolution of",
                "about 15 keV for MeV protons and about 20 keV for MeV",
                "He+ ions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Several experiments were performed in this study to",
                "determine the excitation curves of (p,p), (d,p) and",
                " (alpha,alpha) reactions/scatterings for 12C. The",
                "measurement for the excitation curve was carried out",
                "at a reaction or scattering angle of 150 degrees over",
                "a range of ion energy with small energy increments,",
                "typically of 4 to 5 keV. For each spectrum, the",
                "accumulated charge varied from 5 to 10 microC for",
                "good spectrum statistics. In addition, an angular",
                "distribution for the reaction 12C(d,p)13C at",
                "deuterium ion energy Ed=0.94 MeV was also determined",
                "with steps of 2 degrees over the reaction angles",
                "ranging from 100 to 170 degrees."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The total experimental error for the cross",
                "section data was estimated to  be of the order of 4%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "After the publication, authors noticed that the",
                "energy shifts of the resonant peaks were primarily",
                "due to an inaccurate voltage calibration for the",
                "accelerator system they used. Following a careful",
                "examination and thorough analysis, this shift has",
                "been determined, and revised data sets were published",
                "in the erratum."
              ]
            }
          ],
